Dear Watanabe-san,

I hope this message finds you well. As you know, maintaining a healthy environment for your plants is essential to achieving a higher yield. Today, I would like to share some tips on how you can improve soil fertility and increase the yield of your paddy-rice crop.

Firstly, let's check the soil nitrogen levels. As you may have noticed, it is slightly lower than ideal. Adding a light fertilizer, such as an organic one containing nitrogen, can help balance nitrogen levels in the soil. This can significantly improve plant growth and ultimately increase your yield.

Secondly, it is important to ensure adequate soil phosphorus levels for healthy plant growth. As you may have noticed, your soil phosphorus levels are low. Adding a light fertilizer containing phosphorus can help boost levels in the soil.

Lastly, checking soil potassium levels can also help plants grow stronger. Adding a light fertilizer containing potassium can help balance potassium levels in the soil.

In terms of climate, it is also important to monitor the temperature and humidity levels. As you may have noticed, high temperatures and low humidity levels can affect plant growth. I recommend checking both factors regularly and adjusting accordingly to maintain a suitable environment for your plants.

I hope these tips are helpful for you. Let me know if you have any questions or if there is anything else I can assist you with.

